plan.prompt:
Your name is agent_1. Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Your private information:
{agents->agent_1->private_information}
Your contribution goal:
{agents->agent_1->goal}
Provide an ordered list of primitive moves (one move per line) in the exact format 'agent_1: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'. Only include moves for disks you are allowed to move. Ensure every move respects the Tower of Hanoi rules. If you need to leave notes about dependencies on agent_2 moves, keep them brief and clearly marked as comments prefixed by '#'.

Your name is agent_2. Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Your private information:
{agents->agent_2->private_information}
Your contribution goal:
{agents->agent_2->goal}
Provide an ordered list of primitive moves (one move per line) in the exact format 'agent_2: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'. Only include moves for disks you are allowed to move. Ensure every move respects the Tower of Hanoi rules. If you need to leave notes about dependencies on agent_1 moves, keep them brief and clearly marked as comments prefixed by '#'.

pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator. Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Agent reports:
{moves_agent_1}
{moves_agent_2}
Your private information:
{agents->orchestrator->private_information}
Your goal:
{agents->orchestrator->goal}
Step by step, integrate the agents' move lists, correct or fill any missing moves necessary to respect Tower of Hanoi rules and agent restrictions, and produce:
1) The final ordered list of primitive moves in the exact format 'agent_i: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'.
2) The PDDL domain and PDDL problem targeting the FastDownward solver, with the domain enclosed between <domain></domain> and the problem between <problem></problem>.
Ensure actions corresponding to different agents remain distinct in the PDDL and the plan listing.
